parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Loose or Improperly Assembled Steering Components
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Loose or improperly assembled steering components can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or difficulty maneuvering the vehicle.
symptoms: vibration in the wheel while turning

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the rack and pinion steering can cause loss of steering control, leading to accidents or difficulty maneuvering the vehicle.
symptoms: vibration in the wheel while turning

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the power steering line can cause loss of power steering assist, leading to increased effort required to steer the vehicle, which can cause accidents or difficulty maneuvering the vehicle.
symptoms: increased effort required to steer the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause a loss of brake function, leading to accidents or injuries. Corrosion of the unibody can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, making it unsafe to drive.
symptoms: Brake lines need to be replaced multiple times
brake pedal goes to the floor
vehicle is unable to be driven.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brakes can cause accidents or injuries, especially if the brake pedal goes to the floor or the brakes pulsate when applied.
symptoms: Brake pedal goes to the floor
vehicle slides when brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause engine coolant and oil to mix, leading to engine damage, overheating, and potentially causing a crash.
symptoms: engine stalling or failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle stalling unexpectedly can cause a crash, and the no-start condition can leave the driver stranded.
A disconnected engine coolant line can cause the vehicle to overheat, leading to engine damage and potentially causing a crash.
